<br>
atm almost every quest i can think of is the same.  the only variant is where the quest items are, which mobs drop them and what kind of faction you need.  the difficulty of a quest is based on the randomness of a quest drop/quest mob or the level of the mob that drops the quest items.<br>
<br>
sometimes theres a little twist to it.  maybe you have to charm a mob.  maybe you have to do a sneak turn in.  maybe you have to raise your poison/brewing/tailoring skill to get the quest item, and then proceed to killing the mobs again.<br>
<br>
the rogue epic was genious.  you get to go pick pocket mobs.  you get to hide/sneak into a fully popped hate, metal gear solid style watching for roaming lichs, carefuly maneuvering yourself to get your hate book.  you had to fight renux a hard hitting mob (for its time), and having you use ingenious tactics, like kiting a mob around with mage pets or fear kiting it.  you had to do a sneak turn in to a kos mob to pop your epic mob and having to kill it.<br>
<br>
what kind of response did that type of quest get with the general player community?<br>
<br>
complaints about how it was too easy, remarks like freebringer and the like.  if it doesn't require killing mob after mob after mob, people say it's the same hack and slash game.  if it doesn't require it, people say it's too easy.<br>
<br>
-------------------------<br>
<br>
